ndia%2Farticle66575057.ece%5C%22%3Eput%20the%20%E2%80%9Cborder%20question%E2%80%9D%20in%20a%20proper%20place%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20larger%20framework%20of%20bilateral%20relations%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%99s%20counter-position%20of%20the%20relationship%20being%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Flatest%2F1048252%2Frelations-with-china-abnormal-due-to-beijings-violation-of-border-agreements-says-s-jaishankar%5C%22%3Eabnormal%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20until%20resolution%20of%20the%20border%20standoff%2C%20points%20to%20a%20completely%20divergent%20perception%20on%20both%20sides%20on%20how%20to%20take%20the%20relationship%20forward.%20This%20divergence%20is%20not%20the%20result%20of%20the%20individual%20judgment%20of%20leaders%20on%20both%20sides%20but%20precipitated%20by%20several%20structural%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOne%20of%20the%20lenses%20to%20understand%20the%20Sino-%3Cspan%3EIndian%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0relationship%20is%20through%20the%20triangle%20of%20the%20US-%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%93%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0framework.%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%98s%20principal%20concern%20during%20the%20Cold%20War%20era%20was%20to%20ensure%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndian%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0neutrality%20in%20its%20great%20power%20competition%20with%20the%20US%20and%20USSR.%20After%20the%20demise%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20in%201991%20and%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20unipolar%20moment%2C%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%98s%20principal%20objective%20was%20to%20secure%20its%20periphery%20to%20blunt%20any%20possible%20US%20moves%20to%20instigate%20regime%20change%20in%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20This%20prompted%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0to%20engage%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0through%20the%201993%20BPAT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fon-the-india-china-border-disengagement-is-not-resolution%5C%22%3EOn%20the%20India-China%20Border%2C%20Disengagement%20Is%20Not%20Resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENow%20that%20the%20US%20unipolar%20moment%20has%20passed%20and%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%20herself%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20pole%20in%20a%20direct%20confrontation%20with%20the%20US%20for%20global%20hegemony%2C%20its%20policy%20goal%20has%20changed%20from%20securing%20its%20periphery%20to%20expanding%20its%20influence.%20This%20is%20illustrated%20by%20%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%98s%20increasingly%20hostile%20posture%20in%20its%20territorial%20disputes%20with%20its%20neighbours%2C%20be%20it%20Philippines%2C%20Vietnam%20or%20%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Sino-%3Cspan%3EIndian%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0case%20is%20unique%20due%20to%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%99s%20stated%20objective%20of%20multipolarity.%20And%20given%20the%20size%20of%20its%20territory%2C%20population%20and%20economy%2C%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0has%20the%20unique%20ability%20to%20act%20as%20a%20swing%20state%20in%20Sino-US%20competition.%20The%20core%20problem%20which%20has%20stymied%20the%20Sino-%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0relationship%20is%20Bejing%E2%80%99s%20inability%20to%20view%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%20as%20an%20independent%20actor.%20The%20patronising%20rhetoric%20coming%20out%20from%20%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0since%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fchina-india-bhutan-doklam-standoff-border-dispute%5C%22%3E2017%20Doklam%20incident%3C%2Fa%3E%20reflects%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%98s%20continuing%20view%20of%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0as%20a%20piece%20in%20the%20global%20chessboard%20rather%20than%20as%20a%20player%20with%20whom%20it%20can%20meaningfully%20engage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThis%20has%20created%20a%20rather%20paradoxical%20situation%20where%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0feels%20it%20has%20to%20align%20more%20closely%20with%20the%20United%20States%20in%20order%20to%20bolster%20its%20bargaining%20position%20vis-a-vis%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20In%20turn%2C%20this%20closer%20alignment%20is%20viewed%20by%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0as%20the%20validation%20of%20its%20perception%20that%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0is%20not%20an%20autonomous%20player.%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%98s%20policy%20of%20%E2%80%9Cstrategic%20autonomy%E2%80%9D%20means%20it%20is%20averse%20to%20forming%20any%20treaty%20relation%20with%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20unlike%20Japan%20or%20South%20Korea.%20However%2C%20given%20its%20rapidly%20deteriorating%20relations%20with%20%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20closer%20engagement%20with%20the%20United%20States%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Chedge%E2%80%9D%20which%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0is%20pursuing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0has%20invested%20its%20geo-political%20capital%20in%20transforming%20the%20%E2%80%9CQUAD%E2%80%9D%20from%20a%20loose%20acronym%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Csummit%20level%E2%80%9D%20institution.%20In%20the%20maritime%20domain%2C%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20put%20the%20%E2%80%9CIndo-Pacific%E2%80%9D%20construct%20at%20the%20centre-piece%20of%20its%20%3Cspan%3EIndian%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0Ocean%20strategy.%20Although%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20has%20specifically%20called%20the%20%E2%80%9CIndo-Pacific%E2%80%9D%20a%20geographical%20construct%2C%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0views%20the%20%E2%80%98free%20and%20open%20Indo-Pacific%E2%80%99%20as%20another%20US%20instigated%20attempt%20to%20contain%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0in%20the%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndian%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Ocean%20by%20exploiting%20its%20vulnerabilities%20along%20choke%20points%20like%20the%20Strait%20of%20Malacca.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-china-the-glue-driving-india-us-ties-biden-betting-on-modi-staying-in-power%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98China%20the%20Glue%20Driving%20India-US%20Ties%3B%20Biden%20Betting%20on%20Modi%20Staying%20in%20Power%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThis%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndian%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0strategy%20of%20%E2%80%9Chedging%E2%80%9D%20has%20its%20own%20pitfalls%20in%20case%20a%20%3Cem%3Emodus%20vivendi%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20reached%20between%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20the%20United%20States%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9CG-2%E2%80%9D%20of%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasia.nikkei.com%2FEditor-s-Picks%2FChina-up-close%2FAnalysis-After-a-decade-Xi-floats-G2-world-with-U.S.-again%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20giants%20managing%20global%20affairs%20together%3C%2Fa%3E.%20President%20Xi%20proposed%20the%20G2%20concept%20to%20Barack%20Obama%20when%20he%20was%20US%20president%20but%20that%20proposal%20did%20not%20get%20very%20far.%20If%20revived%2C%20however%2C%20the%20US%20commitment%20towards%20%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0may%20dwindle.%20On%20its%20part%2C%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0is%20also%20making%20a%20risky%20bet%20by%20keeping%20the%20LAC%20hot%20%E2%80%93%20given%20that%20it%20may%20face%20its%20own%20%E2%80%9Ctwo%20front%E2%80%9D%20situation%20with%20the%20volatile%20situation%20in%20both%20Taiwan%20strait%20and%20the%20Himalayas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EGiven%20the%20dire%20consequences%20of%20the%20protracted%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20the%20world%2C%20especially%20the%20global%20south%2C%20cannot%20afford%20another%20theatre%20of%20war%20in%20Asia.%20This%20requires%20not%20just%20a%20softening%20of%20%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%98s%20belligerent%20posture%20but%20also%20a%20willingness%20to%20engage%20in%20dialogue%20with%20its%20neighbors%20in%20a%20constructive%20manner.%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%98s%20own%20position%20carries%20an%20inherent%20contradiction%20where%20it%20presents%20its%20territorial%20integrity%20as%20%E2%80%9Cnon-negotiable%E2%80%9D%20and%20expects%20other%20countries%20to%20view%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChinese%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0encroachments%20on%20their%20borders%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cproper%20perspective%E2%80%9D.%20This%20patronizing%20attitude%20can%20be%20seen%20in%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%98s%20territorial%20dispute%20with%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20its%20dispute%20in%20the%20South%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0policy%20has%20its%20own%20shortcomings.%20For%20example%2C%20despite%20much%20rhetoric%2C%20the%20trade%20deficit%20with%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0is%20ballooning.%20Knee-jerk%20reactions%20like%20banning%20Tik-Tok%20should%20be%20substituted%20by%20structural%20reforms%20to%20ensure%20a%20balance%20in%20economic%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EDespite%20many%20divergences%2C%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%20have%20much%20more%20in%20common.%20For%20example%2C%20both%20have%20quite%20similar%20positions%20in%20climate%20negotiations%2C%20IMF%20reforms%20etc.%20During%20the%20Wuhan%20and%20Mahabalipuram%20summits%2C%20both%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20and%20President%20Xi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F31938%2F2nd_IndiaChina_Informal_Summit%5C%22%3Etalked%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20%E2%80%9Cstrategic%20communication%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20make%20sure%20that%20%E2%80%9Cdifferences%20don%E2%80%99t%20become%20disputes%E2%80%9D.%20This%20approach%20needs%20to%20be%20implemented%20since%20the%20world%20is%20big%20enough%20to%20accommodate%20the%20aspirations%20of%20both%20%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan