rmat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22942%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESupreme%20Court%20Associate%20Justice%20Sonia%20Sotomayor%20poses%20for%20an%20official%20portrait%20on%20October%207%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Wong%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJust%203%20out%20of%20the%209%20Supreme%20Court%20Justices%20are%20liberals.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESonia%20Sotomayor%20and%20Elena%20Kagan%20are%20in%20excellent%20health%2C%20but%20there's%20always%20risks%20as%20people%20age.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUnless%20Democrats%20are%20willing%20to%20risk%20a%207-2%20GOP-held%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20it%20might%20be%20time%20to%20consider%20retirement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20Democrats%20are%20worried%20about%20Joe%20Biden's%20age%20as%20he%20heads%20into%20the%20next%20election.%20This%20is%2C%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20a%20valid%20concern%3A%20there's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgerontocracy-united-states-government-red-white-gray-2022-9%5C%22%3Elots%20of%20reasons%20to%20be%20concerned%20about%20the%20rising%20age%20of%20the%20American%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20rigors%20of%20the%20presidency%20are%20well-known.%20However%2C%20Joe%20Biden%20should%20be%20far%20from%20the%20Democrats'%20biggest%20worry%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20age.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20it%20stands%2C%20GOP-appointed%20justices%20control%20six%20out%20of%20nine%20seats%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Earlier%20in%20his%20term%2C%20President%20Biden%20appointed%20then-51%20year%20old%20Associate%20Justice%20Ketanji%20Brown%20Jackson%20to%20fill%20the%20seat%20previously%20held%20by%20retiring%20Justice%20Stephen%20Breyer%2C%20who%20was%20then%2083.%20The%20other%20liberal%20justices%2C%20Elena%20Kagan%20(63)%20and%20Sonia%20Sotomayor%20(68)%20were%20appointed%20by%20President%20Barack%20Obama.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlready%2C%20this%20minority%20is%20being%20felt.%20The%20conservative%20wing%20of%20the%20court%20can%20pursue%20judgments%20sufficiently%20far%20to%20the%20right%20that%20they%20can%20lose%20one%20of%20their%20numbers%20and%20still%20pass%205-4.%20This%20was%20felt%20most%20acutely%20when%20the%20five%20most%20conservative%20justices%20%E2%80%94%20three%20of%20whom%20were%20appointed%20by%20President%20Donald%20Trump%3A%20one%20because%20the%20GOP-held%20Senate%20refused%20to%20consider%20an%20Obama%20appointee%2C%20and%20another%20because%20Justice%20Ruth%20Bader%20Ginsberg%20died%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-abortion-decision-final-ruling-scotus-roe-v-wade-2022-6%5C%22%3Eoverturned%3C%2Fa%3E%20Roe%20v.%20Wade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20unexpected%20vacancy%20caused%20by%20the%20death%20or%20sudden%20retirement%20of%20a%20liberal%20justice%20under%20a%20Republican%20president%20or%20a%20GOP-controlled%20Senate%20would%20be%20catastrophic%20for%20Democrats.%20Already%2C%20a%206-3%20court%20means%20that%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future%20liberal%20policies%20will%20have%20a%20difficult%20time%20in%20the%20American%20judicial%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%207-2%20court%20would%20make%20that%20disadvantage%20a%20generational%20one.%20Some%20current%20GOP%20justices%20have%20indicated%20that%20things%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Froe-wade-loving-virginia-interracial-marriage-scotus-overturns-2022-6%5C%22%3Einterracial%20marriage%20or%20same-sex%20marriage%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20safe%20despite%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%20precedent%3B%20perhaps%20a%20new%20colleague%20might%20not%20agree.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20are%20the%20chances%20of%20a%207-2%20GOP%20Supreme%20Court%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20can%20approximate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprobability-a-supreme-court-justice-dies-after-the-2024-election-2023-9%5C%22%3Ethe%20general%20probabilities%20of%20this%20risk%20using%20actuarial%20data.%3C%2Fa%3E%20It's%20far%20from%20perfect%2C%20given%20that%20these%20are%20wealthy%20lawyers%20with%20excellent%20health%20care%20and%20not%20exactly%20%26quot%3Baverage.%26quot%3B%20But%20it's%20an%20effective%20ballpark%20estimate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20a%20group%20of%20women%20aged%2069%2C%2063%20and%2052%20years%20old%2C%20we'd%20expect%20that%20there's%20an%2018%25%20chance%20that%20someone%20will%20die%20within%20the%20next%20five%20and%20a%20half%20years%2C%20which%20would%20take%20us%20to%20the%20end%20of%20the%20next%20president's%20term%20in%20January%202029.%20Subtracting%20the%204%25%20chance%20of%20a%20death%20within%20the%20next%201.5%20years%2C%20through%20the%20end%20of%20this%20Biden%20term%2C%20that%20brings%20us%20to%20a%2014%25%20chance%20that%20at%20least%20one%20of%20those%20three%20hypothetical%20people%20dies%20during%20the%20time%20the%20next%20U.S.%20president%20will%20be%20serving.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIs%20that%20especially%20high%3F%20No%2C%20absolutely%20not.%20It's%20well%20below%20the%2040%25%20chance%20their%20GOP%20counterparts%20have.%20But%20the%20question%20isn't%20%3Cem%3Eis%20it%20likely%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eit's%2C%20%3Cem%3Ewhat%20is%20the%20acceptable%20level%20of%20risk%20for%20liberals%20of%20most%20likely%20losing%20the%20court%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20lives%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%2014%25%20chance%20is%20low%20but%20not%20rare.%20It's%20very%20nearly%20the%20odds%20of%20rolling%20a%20one%20on%20a%20six-sided%20die.%20It's%20the%20likelihood%20a%20day%20in%20Phoenix%2C%20Arizona%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.move.org%2Fsunniest-cities-america%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20bit%20cloudy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%2014%25%20chance%20of%20that%20happening%20is%3Cem%3E%20five%20times%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20chance%20of%20rolling%20snake%20eyes%20in%20a%20game%20of%20craps%2C%20an%20event%20which%20happens%20all%20the%20time.%20Any%20%3Cem%3EDungeons%20%26amp%3B%20Dragons%3C%2Fem%3E%20player%20would%20balk%20at%20a%20roll%20where%20there's%20a%20three-in-twenty%20chance%20of%20a%20TPK.%20A%2014%25%20chance%20is%20very%2C%20very%20possible.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20can%20the%20Democrats%20lower%20that%20chance%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%207-2%20Supreme%20Court%20split%20would%20mean%20anywhere%20from%20years%20to%20decades%20before%20the%20liberal%20side%20is%20likely%20even%20able%20to%20get%20back%20to%20four%20justices%2C%20and%20perhaps%20even%20longer.%20It%20would%20be%20tremendously%20bad%20luck%2C%20but%20then%20again%2C%20anyone%20who%20thinks%20that%20Democrats%20have%20had%20good%20luck%20at%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20delusional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20light%20of%20that%2C%20what%20should%20the%20Democrats%20do%20to%20minimize%20the%20risk%20of%20that%20outcome%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden's%20got%20a%20Democratic%20Senate%20right%20now.%20Who%20knows%20when%20Democrats%20will%20again%20hold%20both%20the%20presidency%20and%20the%20senate%3A%20the%202024%20Senate%20map%20looks%20rough%20for%20Democrats%2C%20and%20the%20presidential%20election%20could%20be%20close.%20We%20could%20be%20talking%20anywhere%20from%20two%20to%20six%20or%20even%20eight%20or%20ten%20years%20here.%20If%20it%20all%20sounds%20rather%20familiar%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgai.georgetown.edu%2Fginsburg-retirement-and-senate-confirmations%2F%5C%22%3EI%20wonder%20why%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20there%20are%20ways%20to%20reduce%20the%2014%25%20chance.%20If%20instead%20of%20a%2068-year-old%20woman%2C%20there%20was%2C%20say%2C%20a%2050-year-old%20woman%20serving%20on%20the%20court%2C%20the%20risk%20drops%20six%20points%20to%208%25.%20If%20both%20a%2068-year-old%20woman%20and%20a%2063-year-old%20woman%20were%20replaced%20with%2050-year-old%20woman%2C%20it%20drops%20to%20about%205%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20sure%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20arguments%20against%20encouraging%20Justice%20Sonia%20Sotomayor%20or%20Justice%20Elena%20Kagan%20to%20retire.%20They%20can%20%3