%20funds%20in%20banks%E2%80%99%20current%20accounts%20despite%20there%20being%20%E2%80%9Cno%20provision%20in%20government%20accounting%20%E2%80%A6%20rules%20to%20retain%20public%20funds%20outside%20government%20accounts%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERs%20154.94%20crore%20of%20public%20funds%20were%20parked%20in%20these%20accounts%20by%20the%20space%20department%2C%20the%20CAG%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20although%20it%20had%20asked%20the%20department%20to%20close%20the%20accounts%20in%20October%202021%2C%20the%20latter%20had%20failed%20to%20do%20this%20even%20as%20of%20November%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-report-nhai-toll-collection-railway-bharatmala-udan%5C%22%3ENHAI%E2%80%99s%20Tolls%2C%20UDAN%20Delays%2C%20Unsanctioned%20Railway%20Costs%3A%20What%20the%20CAG%20Reports%20Say%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20auditor%20also%20pointed%20to%20a%20case%20where%20two%20Union%20government%20ministries%20failed%20to%20coordinate%20their%20share%20of%20funds%20with%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20in%20respect%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98Rashtriya%20Swachhata%20Kosh%E2%80%99%20(Hindi%20for%20%E2%80%98national%20cleanliness%20fund%E2%80%99)%2C%20out%20of%20which%20the%20sanitation%20and%20urban%20affairs%20ministries%20were%20entitled%20to%2080%25%20and%2020%25%20shares%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20financial%20years%202015-2017%2C%20the%20sanitation%20ministry%20%E2%80%9Cutilised%20the%20entire%20amount%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20fund%2C%20after%20which%20its%20urban%20affairs%20counterpart%20incurred%20an%20adverse%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20balance%20persists%20as%20of%20May%202023%2C%20the%20CAG%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20one%20of%20the%20report%E2%80%99s%20findings%20relates%20to%20cesses%20(a%20kind%20of%20additional%20tax)%20having%20nowhere%20to%20go%20despite%20prior%20approvals%20and%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20the%20CAG%20said%20that%20during%20the%20financial%20year%202021-2022%2C%20Rs%2052%2C732%20crore%20was%20collected%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98health%20and%20education%20cess%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%2060%25%20of%20this%20amount%20(Rs%2031%2C788%20crore)%20was%20transferred%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98Prarambhik%20Shiksha%20Kosh%E2%80%99%20(Hindi%20for%20%E2%80%98primary%20education%20fund%E2%80%99).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20remainder%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20transferred%20to%20two%20other%20funds%3A%20namely%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98Madhyamik%20and%20Uchhatar%20Shiksha%20Kosh%E2%80%99%20(Hindi%20for%20%E2%80%98middle%20and%20higher%20education%20fund%E2%80%99)%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98Pradhan%20Mantri%20Swasthya%20Suraksha%20Nidhi%E2%80%99%20(Hindi%20for%20%E2%80%98prime%20minister%20health%20protection%20fund%E2%80%99).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20audit%20body%20found%20that%20%E2%80%9Cin%20spite%20of%20the%20cabinet%E2%80%99s%20approval%20for%20their%20creation%E2%80%9D%2C%20these%20two%20funds%20%E2%80%9Cwere%20not%20even%20created%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBoth%20are%20yet%20to%20be%20operationalised%20%5Bas%20of%20May%202023%5D%20due%20to%20non-finalisation%20of%20their%20accounting%20procedures%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CAG%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20way%20the%20Union%20government%20used%20footnotes%20in%20its%20finance%20accounts%20made%20its%20finances%20more%20opaque.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20total%20of%20258%20footnotes%20had%20been%20included%20for%20disclosing%20additional%20information%20in%20%5Bthe%20finance%20accounts%5D%20for%20FY%202021-22.%20However%2C%20these%20footnotes%20did%20not%20disclose%20the%20complete%20picture%20of%20the%20finances%20of%20the%20Union%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20Report%2021%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20these%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20the%20government%20underreported%20some%20of%20its%20liabilities%20by%20over%20Rs%2021%2C000%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGujarat%20government%20didn%E2%80%99t%20prepare%20state%20forest%20policy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20performance%20audit%20report%20by%20the%20CAG%20has%20found%20that%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20had%20not%20prepared%20a%20state%20forest%20policy%20as%20of%202021%20even%20though%20the%20National%20Forest%20Commission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fahmedabad%2Fmeagre-funds-protection-wildlife-sanctuaries-gujarat-cag-8942646%2F%5C%22%3Erecommended%20all%20states%20to%20do%20so%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20report%20was%20submitted%20to%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20last%20month%20and%20was%20tabled%20in%20its%20legislative%20assembly%20on%20Saturday%20(September%2016).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20Gujarat%E2%80%99s%20forest%20department%20had%20also%20not%20established%20a%20mechanism%20for%20ensuring%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20National%20Forest%20Policy%20and%20National%20Wildlife%20Action%20Plan%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fcag-report-pulls-up-gujarat-forest-dept-for-shortcomings-ignoring-isro-report-on-12-potential-wildlife-corridors%2F1765301%2F%5C%22%3EPTI%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20government%20had%20also%20not%20declared%20critical%20wildlife%20habitats%20in%20sanctuaries%20despite%2014%20years%20having%20passed%20following%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act%2C%20the%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20report%20said%20according%20to%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20auditor%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fcag-report-pulls-up-gujarat-forest-dept-for-shortcomings-ignoring-isro-report-on-12-potential-wildlife-corridors%2F1765301%2F%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20ISRO%20had%20identified%2012%20wildlife%20corridors%20in%20Gujarat%20in%202014%20and%202017%2C%20following%20which%20it%20made%20recommendations%20to%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20forest%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20department%20%E2%80%9Cneither%20conducted%20any%20study%20itself%20to%20identify%20the%20precise%20corridors%20nor%20took%20cognisance%20of%20the%20scientific%20study%20conducted%20by%20ISRO%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Faudit-report%2Fdetails%2F119337%5C%22%3Ethe%20CAG%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKerala%20revenue%20departments%20%E2%80%98tardy%E2%80%99%20in%20pursuing%20arrears%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country%E2%80%99s%20apex%20audit%20institute%20also%20prepared%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Faudit-report%2Fdetails%2F119301%5C%22%3Ecompliance%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Kerala%20government%E2%80%99s%20revenue%20sector%2C%20which%20it%20sent%20to%20the%20state%20government%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKerala%E2%80%99s%20legislative%20assembly%20tabled%20the%20compliance%20report%20on%20Thursday%20(August%2014).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20finds%20that%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20revenue%20sector%20has%20racked%20up%20arrears%20worth%20Rs%2028%2C258%20crore%20as%20of%20March%202022%2C%20which%20amounted%20to%20a%20significant%2024%25%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20total%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20necessitates%20urgent%20intervention%20from%20the%20government%20to%20clear%20the%20outstanding%20arrears%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CAG%20said%20in%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20absence%20of%20prompt%20reporting%20of%20arrears%20to%20%5Bthe%5D%20revenue%20department%20and%20tardy%20pursuance%20by%20the%20departments%20concerned%20for%20realising%20the%20arrears%20are%20the%20main%20reasons%20for%20the%20huge%20pendency%20of%20arrears.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fquestions-cag-auditors-failed-to-probe-in-its-mizoram-report%5C%22%3EThe%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20Mizoram%20Audit%20Report%20Leads%20to%20Numerous%20Questions%2C%20Some%20on%20its%20Own%20Processes%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CAG%20also%20provided%20a%20breakdown%20of%20the%20Rs%2028%2C258%20crore%20in%20arrears%2C%20which%20says%20that%20Kerala%E2%80%99s%20goods%20and%20services%20tax%20department%20holds%20the%20highest%20proportion%20of%20arrears%20at%20Rs%2013%2C410%20crore%20(or%2047%25)%20of%20the%20total.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Kerala%E2%80%99s%20finance%20minister%20K.N.%20Balagopal%20justified%20his%20government%E2%80%99s%20measures%2C%20saying%20that%20tax%20arrears%20the%20state%20was%20supposed%20to%20collect%20had%20decreased%20by%20Rs%20420%20crore%20over%20one%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUsually%2C%20the%20deficits%20in%20tax%20departments%20never%20come%20down%2C%20but%20only%20increase.%20But%20this%20year%2C%20there%20is%20a%20reduction%20of%20Rs%20420%20crore%20in%20tax%20deficits%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20tax%20deficits%20during%20the%20last%20financial%20year.%20This%20is%20a%20historical%20achievement%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2Fpti%2Fgovernment-will-take-follow-up-actions-based-on-cag-report-balagopal%2F%5C%22%3EPTI%20quoted%20Balagopal%20as%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695029799000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F06163312%2FCAG-building-II.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-finds-tardy-performance-by-gujarat-and-kerala-govts-and-holes-in-centres-accounting%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20found%20multiple%20issues%20in%20the%20Centre's%20reporting%20practices%2C%20including%20funds%20being%20parked%20in%20unauthorised%20accounts%20and%20incomplete%20disclosures%20due%20to%20opaque%20use%20of%20footnotes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-finds-tardy-performance-by-gujarat-and-kerala-govts-and-holes-in-centres-accounting%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%226%20Creatures%20Guard%206%20Gates%20Of%20New%20Parliament%20Building%2C%20What%20They%20Symbolise%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20Parliament%20building%2C%20where%20proceedings%20will%20begin%20tomorrow%2C%20has%20six%20gates%20named%20after%20creatures%20--%20some%20real%2C%20others%20mythological.%20Each%20of%20these%20creatures%20signifies%20different%20aspects%20of%20the%20Parliament%20that%20represents%20140%20crore%20Indians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20six%20gates%20are%20Gaja%20Dwar%2C%20Ashwa%20Dwar%2C%20Garuda%20Dwar%2C%20Makar%20Dwar%2C%20Shardula%20Dwar%20and%20Hamsa%20Dwar.%20Each%20door%20boasts%20a%20sculpture%20of%20the%20creature%20it%20is%20named%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Gaja%20Dwar%20is%20named%20after%20the%20elephant%2C%20which%20represents%20intellect%2C%20memory%2C%20wealth%20and%20wisdom.%20This%20gate%20is%20on%20the%20north%20side%20of%20the%20building.%20The%20north%2C%20according%20to%20vaastu%20shashtra%2C%20is%20associated%20with%20Mercury%2C%20believed%20to%20be%20a%20source%20of%20intellect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElephant%20motifs%20are%20common%20on%20gates.%20According%20to%20vaastu%20shastra%2C%20they%20are%20said%20to%20bring%20prosperity%20and%20happiness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAshwa%20Dwar%20is%20named%20after%20the%20horse.%20A%20horse%20symbolises%20power%2C%20strength%20and%20courage%20--%20qualities%20desirable%20in%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20gate%20is%20named%20after%20Garuda%20-%20the%20king%20of%20birds.%20Garuda%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20the%20mount%20of%20Lord%20Vishnu.%20Its%20association%20with%20Lord%20Vishnu%20--%20the%20preserver%20in%20the%20Hindu%20trinity%20--%20makes%20Garuda%20a%20symbol%20of%20power%20and%20dharma%20(duty).%20This%20also%20explains%20why%20it%20is%20used%20on%20insignia%20of%20several%20countries.%20The%20Garuda%20gate%20is%20the%20eastern%20entrance%20of%20the%20new%20Parliament%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMakara%20Dwar%20is%20named%20after%20the%20legendary%20sea%20creature%20that%20is%20a%20combination%20of%20different%20animals.%20A%20common%20motif%20for%20entrances%2C%20Makara%20sculptures%20are%20seen%20in%20Hindu%20and%20Buddhist%20monuments%20spread%20across%20South%20and%20Southeast%20Asia.%20On%20one%20hand%2C%20Makara%20as%20the%20combination%20of%20different%20creature%20represents%20India's%20unity%20in%20diversity.%20And%20on%20the%20other%2C%20Makara%20sculptures%20at%20doorways%20are%20seen%20as%20protectors.%20The%20Makara%20Dwar%20faces%20the%20entrance%20to%20the%20old%20Parliament%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fifth%20gate%20is%20named%20after%20another%20mythological%20creature%20-%20Shardula%2C%20which%20has%20the%20body%20of%20a%20lion%2C%20but%20the%20head%20of%20a%20horse%2C%20elephant%20or%20parrot.%20The%20government%20note%20says%20the%20presence%20of%20Shardula%20on%20the%20new%20parliament%20building's%20gate%20symbolises%20the%20power%20of%20the%20people%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sixth%20gate%20of%20Parliament%20is%20Hamsa%20Dwar%20is%20named%20after%20the%20swan.%20Hamsa%20is%20the%20mount%20of%20Saraswati%2C%20the%20Hindu%20goddess%20of%20knowledge.%20Hamsa's%20flight%20symbolises%20moksha%2C%20or%20meaning%20the%20liberation%20of%20the%20soul%20from%20the%20cycle%20of%20birth%20and%20death.%20The%20Hamsa%20sculpture%20on%20the%20Parliament's%20gate%20is%20a%20symbol%20of%20self-realisation%20and%20wisdom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695029100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fpmjt95s_parliament-sculpture_625x300_18_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-parliament-building-special-session-6-creatures-guard-6-gates-of-new-parliament-building-what-they-symbolise-4400450%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20Parliament%20building%2C%20where%2