on%20to%20boycott%2014%20television%20anchors%20who%20have%20been%20identified%20by%20name%20raises%20moral%20and%20ethical%20concerns%20%E2%80%93%20is%20it%20fitting%20in%20a%20democracy%20for%20politicians%20to%20boycott%20fellow%20citizens%3F%20Perhaps%2C%20equally%20importantly%2C%20Ram%2C%20the%20former%20editor-in-chief%20and%20publisher%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20says%20%E2%80%9Ca%20more%20subtle%20approach%20could%20have%20suited%20the%20INDIA%20Alliance%20better%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20would%20be%20smarter%20for%20the%20alliance%20to%20leave%20it%20to%20individuals%20to%20decline%20and%20accept%E2%80%9D%20any%20request%20to%20appear%20on%20shows%20conducted%20by%20these%2014%20anchors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Ram%20made%20a%20point%20of%20saying%20that%20%E2%80%9Cbias%20is%20common%20in%20journalism%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20%E2%80%9Cyou%20can%E2%80%99t%20discriminate%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20bias%E2%80%9D.%20However%2C%20he%20said%20communalism%2C%20hate%20against%20Muslims%20and%20bullying%20is%20a%20different%20matter.%20But%20he%20repeated%20his%20point%20that%20it%20might%20have%20been%20smarter%20for%20the%20alliance%20to%20simply%2C%20politely%20and%20quietly%20refuse%20invitations%20from%20anchors%20they%20do%20not%20like%20rather%20than%20publicly%20announce%20a%20boycott.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20from%20the%20point%20of%20view%20of%20channel%20owners%2C%20Ram%20categorically%20said%20%E2%80%9Cno%20self-respecting%20channel%20should%20allow%20a%20politician%20to%20decide%20who%20will%20be%20the%20journalists%20to%20talk%20to%20him%E2%80%9D.%20This%20means%20that%20channel%20owners%20should%20take%20a%20strong%20stand%20both%20in%20defence%20of%20their%20anchors%20(who%20have%20been%20boycotted)%20and%20in%20defence%20of%20their%20right%20to%20adopt%20whatever%20political%20position%20or%20stance%20they%20want%20for%20their%20channel.%20But%20will%