y.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235725833%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Britain%E2%80%99s%20public%20service%20broadcasters%20(PSBs)%20are%20developing%20a%20new%20free%20TV%20service%20that%20will%20deliver%20live%20TV%20over%20broadband.%20Set%20for%20launch%20in%202024%2C%20the%20service%2C%20called%20Freely%2C%C2%A0will%20allow%20viewers%20to%20browse%20and%20watch%20live%20TV%20channels%20together%20with%20on-demand%20content%20streamed%20to%20their%20smart%20TV%20via%20the%20internet.%20Freely%20will%20be%20built-in%20to%20the%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Naman%20Ramachandran%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fglobal%2Fuk-live-tv-broadband-freely-1235725833%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fglobal%2Fuk-live-tv-broadband-freely-1235725833%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fglobal%2Fuk-live-tv-broadband-freely-1235725833%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Exclusive%3A%20Vajpayee%20Govt%20Didn't%20Object%20to%20UK%20Report%20That%202002%20Riots%20Were%20'Pre-Planned'%2C%20Cops%20'Told%20Not%20to%20Act'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18033838%2Ffco-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ELondon%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20objecting%20to%20the%20leaking%20of%20an%20investigative%20report%20into%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20riots%20by%20British%20diplomats%2C%20the%20BJP-led%20government%20of%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Edid%20not%20contest%20its%20main%20findings%20that%20the%20anti-Muslim%20pogrom%20in%20Gujarat%20in%202002%20was%20%E2%80%9Cpre-planned%E2%80%9D%2C%20that%20Sangh%20parivar%20outfits%20like%20the%20Vishwa%20Hindu%20Parishad%20had%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20the%20targeting%20of%20Muslims%20and%20that%20the%20police%20had%20been%20specifically%20instructed%20not%20to%20act%20against%20the%20killers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20indicated%20in%20the%20minutes%20of%20an%20official%20phone%20conversation%20on%20the%20matter%20between%20Jaswant%20Singh%2C%20then%20India%E2%80%99s%20external%20affairs%20minister%2C%20and%20his%20United%20Kingdom%20counterpart%2C%20Jack%20Straw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Gujarat%20government%20was%20headed%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3ENarendra%20Modi%20at%20the%20time%20and%20the%20full%20British%20report%20concluded%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Cdirectly%20responsible%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpre-planned%E2%80%9D%202002%20Gujarat%20riots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20British%20diplomats%20who%20prepared%20the%202002%20report%20also%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20VHP%20(Vishwa%20Hindu%20Parishad)%20and%20its%20allies%20acted%20with%20the%20support%20of%20the%20state%20government.%20They%20could%20not%20have%20inflicted%20so%20much%20damage%20without%20the%20climate%20of%20impunity%20created%20by%20the%20state%20government.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Singh-Straw%20telephone%20conversation%20took%20place%20on%20April%2016%2C%202002%20%E2%80%93%20one%20day%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sabrang.com%2Fpoll04%2Fquotes%2F021104vaj.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eafter%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20published%20a%20story%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20leaked%20diplomatic%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20hitherto%20classified%2C%20publicly%20unseen%20British%20foreign%20office%20record%20of%20the%20conversation%20was%20obtained%20through%20a%20Freedom%20of%20Information%20Act%20request%20in%20Britain%20(which%20corresponds%20to%20securing%20information%20via%20India%E2%80%99s%20RTI%20Act).%20Sections%20of%20the%20document%20were%20redacted%20by%20the%20foreign%20office%20before%20release%20but%20the%20Gujarat-related%20paragraphs%20are%20there%20in%20full.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20clear%20if%20Jaswant%20Singh%20had%20read%20the%20full%20British%20report%20%E2%80%93%20which%20directly%20held%20Modi%20culpable%20%E2%80%93%20before%20he%20had%20his%20conversation%20with%20Straw%20or%20was%20merely%20relying%20on%20the%20limited%20but%20damning%20details%20published%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEither%20way%2C%20the%20Indian%20foreign%20minister%20chose%20not%20to%20contest%20the%20leaked%20findings%20but%20instead%20confined%20his%20objections%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20report%E2%80%99s%20contents%20had%20found%20their%20way%20into%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20the%20only%20point%20on%20which%20he%20accused%20the%20British%20report%20of%20failing%20to%20ensure%20accurate%20facts%20was%20on%20the%20death%20toll%20%E2%80%93%20and%20not%20on%20its%20primary%20finding%20about%20the%20role%20played%20by%20the%20Gujarat%20police%20(and%20government)%20and%20by%20political%20organisations%20connected%20to%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESingh%20said%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Cextremely%20disappointed%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20British%20findings%20had%20not%20remained%20confidential.%20He%20also%20said%20that%20the%20death%20toll%20cited%20in%20the%20British%20report%20was%20inaccurate.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20British%20probe%20reported%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cextent%20of%20violence%20much%20greater%20than%20reported.%20At%20least%202000%20killed%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20a%20figure%20that%20Singh%20said%20had%20%E2%80%9Chorrified%E2%80%9D%20L.K.%20Advani%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20home%20minister%20at%20the%20time.%20Official%20Indian%20figures%20then%20stood%20at%20850%20dead.%20In%202005%2C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20090226131020%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fnews.indiainfo.com%2F2005%2F05%2F11%2F1105godhra-rs.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20Union%20government%20told%20parliament%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20official%20toll%20was%201%2C044%20dead%20and%20another%20223%20missing.%20As%20many%20as%20919%20women%20had%20been%20widowed.%20In%202009%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2F228-given-up-for-dead-gujarat-riot-toll-up-after-7-year-wait-for-the-missing%2Fcid%2F490944%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGujarat%20government%20put%20the%20official%20death%20toll%20at%201180%3C%2Fa%3E%20including%20all%20missing%20persons.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18032347%2Ffco-collage-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18032347%2Ffco-collage-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18032347%2Ffco-collage-1-300x125.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18032347%2Ffco-collage-1-1024x427.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673438%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERecord%20of%20telephone%20conversation%20between%20India%E2%80%99s%20external%20affairs%20minister%20Jaswant%20Singh%20and%20British%20foreign%20secretary%20Jack%20Straw%2C%20Aril%2016%2C%202002.%20Photo%3A%20FCO%2FAshis%20Ray%2FThe%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20record%20of%20the%20conversation%20indicates%20that%20it%20was%20Straw%20who%20rang%20Singh.%20Straw%E2%80%99s%20private%20secretary%20recorded%20in%20his%20account%20of%20the%20phone%20call%20that%20the%20foreign%20secretary%20%5BStraw%5D%20conveyed%20to%20the%20external%20affairs%20minister%20%5BSingh%5D%20that%20it%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Chelpful%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20former%20to%20say%20%E2%80%9Che%20had%20spoken%20to%20Singh%20and%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20was%20committed%20to%20the%20fullest%20investigation%20into%20the%20events%20in%20Gujarat%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStraw%E2%80%99s%20secretary%20then%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9CSingh%20agreed%E2%80%9D.%20According%20to%20the%20records%2C%20Singh%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20%5BIndian%5D%20government%20had%20given%20instructions%20for%20an%20immediate%20investigation%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20was%20a%20%E2%80%98very%20active%20democratic%20community%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%20He%20added%2C%20though%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20should%20put%20the%20leak%20behind%20us%2C%20but%20draw%20lessons%20from%20the%20incident%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENine%20days%20after%20this%20conversation%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F1%2Fhi%2Fworld%2Fsouth_asia%2F1951471.stm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20BBC%20published%20more%20details%20from%20the%20leaked%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20British%20government%E2%80%99s%20investigation%20into%20the%20riots%20was%20carried%20out%20by%20specialist%20diplomats%20posted%20at%20its%20high%20commission%20in%20Delhi.%20The%20team%20visited%20Gujarat%20from%20April%208-10%2C%202002.%20The%20report%E2%80%99s%20contents%2C%20which%20found%20their%20way%20to%20the%20media%2C%20upset%20the%20Vajpayee%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20terms%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20international%20image%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20on%20April%2015%2C%202002%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20report%20does%20the%20most%20damage%20by%20stating%20that%20the%20post-Godhra%20violence%20in%20Gujarat%20was%20pre-planned.%20If%20the%20Sabarmati%20Express%20tragedy%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20happened%2C%20another%20flashpoint%20would%20have%20been%20created%20to%20justify%20pre-meditated%20violence%20as%20reaction%2C%20the%20report%20says.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20minutes%20of%20the%20phone%20call%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20foreign%20secretary%20expressed%20regret%20that%20a%20high%20commission%20report%20on%20the%20situation%20in%20Gujarat%20had%20leaked.%20But%20he%20underlined%20his%20concern%20about%20the%20violence%20in%20the%20region%2C%20which%20has%20caused%20considerable%20anxiety%20among%20British%20Gujaratis.%20He%20had%20been%20careful%20to%20be%20even-handed%20in%20his%20response%20and%20had%20seen%20delegations%20from%20the%20British%20Muslim%20and%20Hindu%20communities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18033921%2Fst-js.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18033921%2Fst-js.jpg%20700w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18033921%2Fst-js-300x129.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673440%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFormer%20British%20foreign%20secretary%20Jack%20Straw%20(L)%3B%20former%20minister%20of%20external%20affairs%20Jaswant%20Singh%20(R).%20Photos%3A%20Wikimedia%2FUS%20National%20Archives%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSingh%20said%20he%20was%20%E2%80%98extremely%20disappointed%E2%80%99%20at%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20high%20commission.%20He%20accepted%20that%20missions%20sent%20confidential%20reports%20to%20their%20capitals%3B%20the%20%5BIndian%5D%20government%20had%20never%20prevented%20missions%20from%20doing%20their%20work.%20He%20also%20accepted%20that%20we%20%5Bthe%20British%20government%5D%20had%20a%20right%20to%20share%20our%20reports%20with%20EU%20colleagues.%20But%20we%20needed%20to%20ensure%20our%20facts%20were%20accurate.%20Home%20minister%2C%20%5BL.K.%5D%20Advani%2C%20had%20telephoned%20him%20%5BSingh%5D%20yesterday%20and%20was%20horrified%20by%20the%20UK%20figures%20of%20the%20number%20of%20deaths%20in%20Gujarat.%20Many%20would%20see%20this%20as%20the%20UK%20interfering%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20internal%20affairs.%E2%80%9D%20the%20record%20of%20discussion%20further%20stated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20read-out%20of%20the%20telephonic%20dialogue%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20foreign%20secretary%20said%20we%20fully%20respected%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20government%20of%20India.%20We%20%5BBritain%5D%20had%20been%20careful%20not%20to%20criticise%20the%20%5BIndian%5D%20government%20publicly%20but%20to%20make%20our%20representations%20in%20private.%20It%20was%20right%20for%20the%20%5BBritish%5D%20High%20Commission%20to%20make%20an%20assessment%20of%20the%20events%20in%20Gujarat%20which%20were%20causing%20such%20concern%20in%20the%20Indian%20community%20in%20the%20UK.%20The%20foreign%20secretary%2C%20as%20a%20friend%20of%20India%2C%20had%20worked%20hard%20to%20dampen%20feelings%20here%20%5Bin%20Britain%5D%20which%20could%20have%20got%20out%20of%20hand.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fbbc-documentary-narendra-modi-second-episode%5C%22%3EBBC%20Documentary%E2%80%99s%20New%20Episode%20Claims%20Modi%20%E2%80%98Hugely%20Divisive%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98His%20New%20India%E2%80%99%20in%20%E2%80%98Religious%20Turmoil%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%E2%80%98subject%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20top%20secret%20investigation%20report%20sent%20by%20the%20British%20high%20commission%20in%20New%20Delhi%20to%20the%20UK%20Foreign%20Office%20in%20London%20said%20%E2%80%98GUJARAT%20POGROM%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20Singh%20referred%20to%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20British%20high%20commission%2C%20it%20is%20unclear%20from%20the%20memorandum%20on%20the%20phone%20call%20as%20to%20how%20and%20where%20precisely%20the%20investigation%20report%20leaked.%20But%20it%20is%20transparent%20from%20the%20probe%20summary%20that%20it%20was%20circulated%20to%20the%20British%20Home%20Office%20and%20other%20government%20departments%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20various%20UK%20diplomatic%20missions%20in%20the%20region%20and%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20same%20investigation%20report%20became%20the%20centrepiece%20of%20the%20BBC%20revisiting%20the%20issue%20with%20a%20television%20documentary%20broadcast%20in%20January%20this%20year%20on%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20the%20riots.%20Straw%20confirmed%20on%20the%20programme%20that%20he%20had%20indeed%2C%20as%20foreign%20secretary%2C%20ordered%20the%20inquiry%2C%20whose%20report%20eventually%20concluded%20that%20Modi%20was%20%E2%80%98directly%20responsible%E2%80%99%20for%20the%202002%20riots.%20In%20a%20subsequent%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%20The%20Wire%2C%20he%20repeated%20the%20report%E2%80%99s%20main%20conclusions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F8gYkcqExkac%3Fsi%3D8i1I31un5wKc41Wc%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20British%20report%20claimed%20that%20on%20the%20night%20of%20February%2027%2C%202002%20%E2%80%93%20just%20as%20the%20communal%20violence%20in%20Gujarat%20was%20beginning%20%E2%80%93%20Modi%20ordered%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20police%20not%20to%20intervene.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20Muslims%20bore%20the%20brunt%20of%20brutality%20perpetrated%20by%20Hindutva%20zealots.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%20denies%20the%20accusation%20and%20was%20in%202022%20controversially%20absolved%20of%20responsibility%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20BBC%20programme%20highlighted%20the%20fact%20that%20two%20of%20the%20three%20men%20%E2%80%93%20(both%20Indian%20Police%20Service%20officers)%20Sanjiv%20Bhatt%20and%20R.B.%20Sreekumar%20%E2%80%93%20who%20testified%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgujarat-2002-riots-forgery-case-chargesheet-setalvad-sreekumar-bhatt%5C%22%3EModi%20issuing%20instructions%20to%20state%20police%20not%20to%20intervene%20in%20the%20rioting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20had%20cases%20filed%20against%20them%20and%20were%20imprisoned.%20Bhatt%20is%20still%20behind%20bars%20while%20Sreekumar%2C%20who%20was%20arrested%20in%20June%202022%2C%20is%20out%20on%20bail.%20The%20other%2C%20a%20senior%20BJP%20politician%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20Haren%20Pandya%2C%20who%20gave%20evidence%20to%20an%20unofficial%20fact-finding%20panel%2C%20was%20found%20shot%20dead%20in%20seemingly%20mysterious%20circumstances.%20This%20was%20corroborated%20on%20the%20BBC%20programme%20by%20the%20veteran%20BJP%20politician%2C%20Subramaniam%20Swamy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20documentary%20caused%20an%20international%20stir%3B%20the%20external%20affairs%20ministry%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fbbc-documentary-on-pm-modi-a-propaganda-piece-designed-to-push-a-particular-discredited-narrative-says-mea%2Farticle66408578.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattacked%20the%20BBC%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20having%20a%20%E2%80%98colonialist%20mindset%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Soon%20thereafter.%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fwith-bbc-tax-raid-the-modi-cult-makes-india-the-smother-of-democracy%5C%22%3EBBC%E2%80%99s%20offices%20in%20Delhi%20and%20Mumbai%20were%20raided%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Indian%20Income%20Tax%20Department%20on%20grounds%20of%20the%20organisation%20under-declaring%20its%20revenue%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20no%20details%20of%20which%20appear%20to%20have%20been%20made%20available%20for%20professional%20or%20public%20scrutiny.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20then%2C%20a%20BBC%20music%20producer%20was%20denied%20a%20visa%20to%20visit%20India%20for%20a%20holiday%20in%20a%20wildlife%20sanctuary.%20He%2C%20as%20a%20result%2C%20could%20not%20obtain%20a%20refund%20for%20the%20%C2%A34%2C000%20he%20had%20paid%20for%20the%20trip.%20BBC%20sources%20reveal%20this%20is%20not%20the%20only%20instance%20of%20the%20broadcaster%E2%80%99s%20employees%20in%20the%20UK%20being%20effectively%20barred%20from%20entering%20India.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20double%20whammy%2C%20the%20BBC%20was%20in%20July%20criticised%20in%20the%20British%20House%20of%20Commons%20for%20inadequately%20covering%20the%20communal%20and%20ethnic%20violence%20in%20Manipur%20since%20early%20May.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAshis%20Ray%2C%20a%20foreign%20correspondent%20for%2046%20years%2C%20was%20editor-at-large%20of%20CNN.%20He%20can%20be%20followed%20at%20X%20on%20%40ashiscray.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20The%20story%20was%20edited%20at%2011%3A20%20on%20September%2018%20to%20add%20details%20about%20R.B.%20Sreekumar%E2%80%99s%20arrest%20and%20release%20on%20bail.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694990436000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18033838%2Ffco-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fexclusive-vajpayee-govt-didnt-object-to-uk-report-that-2002-riots-were-pre-planned-cops-told-not-to-act%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20minutes%20of%20an%20April%2016%2C%202002%20phone%20call%20between%20former%20external%20affairs%20minister%20Jaswant%20Singh%20and%20his%20UK%20counterpart%20reveal%20the%20BJP-led%20governm